%N A394662 Decimal expansion of the constant characterizing the complexity of the special number field sieve (SNFS) factoring algorithm.
%C A394662 The SNFS algorithm has complexity O(exp(c*(log(n))^(1/3)*(log(log(n))^(2/3)))), where c is the present constant.
%H A394662 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A394662/b394662.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A394662 Carl Pomerance, <a href="https://www.ams.org/notices/199612/pomerance.pdf">A Tale of Two Sieves</a>, Notices of the American Mathematical Society, Volume 43, Number 12, December 1996, pp. 1473-1485 (see p. 1482).
%H A394662 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/NumberFieldSieve.html">Number Field Sieve</a>.
%H A394662 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special_number_field_sieve">Special number field sieve</a>.
%F A394662 Equals (32/9)^(1/3).
%e A394662 1.5262856567377758237440562825862360118878758943839...
%t A394662 First[RealDigits[CubeRoot[32/9], 10, 100]]
